pact of climate on shelter design, identifying four distinct climatic regions and explaining the effect of each on orientation, air movement, site, and materials. He derives principles from biology, engineering, meteorology, and physics, and demonstrates how an analytical approach to climate management can merge into a harmonious and aesthetically sound design concept.This updated edition contains four new essays that provide unique insights on issues of climate design, showing how Olgyay's concepts work in contemporary practice. Ken Yeang, John Reynolds, Victor W. Olgyay, and Donlyn Lyndon explore bioclimatic design, eco design, and rational regionalism, while paying homage to Olgyay's impressive groundwork and contributions to the field of architecture.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aArchitecture and climate. 0aSustainable architecture. 7aARCHITECTURE / Sustainability & Green Design.2bisacsh1 aLyndon, Donlyn, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLyndon, Donlyn.1 aOlgyay, Victor W., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aOlgyay, Victor.1 aReynolds, John, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aReynolds, John.1 aYeang, Ken, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aYeang, Ken.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPrinceton University Press Complete eBook-Package 2016z978311063859240uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781400873685zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781400873685423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781400873685.jpg  a978-3-11-063859-2  Princeton University Press Complete eBook-Package 2016b2016  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_AD  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_AD  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_ESTMAL